mkdir $HOME/.kube/
curl -sfL https://get.k3s.io | sh -s - --docker --write-kubeconfig-mode 644 --write-kubeconfig $HOME/.kube/config

4. Checking nodes after setting up
kubectl get nodes



5. Setting up agent nodes
curl -sfL https://get.k3s.io | K3S_URL=https://<SERVER_NODE_IP>:6443 K3S_TOKEN=<NODE_TOKEN> sh -

5a. if you cannot find the token or sha while running step4 on your master,use the following on master  to regenerate it then execute step 5 on workers again.
kubeadm token create --print-join-command


6. setting up a client who will use your nodes

scp $HOME/.kube/config user@<client-machine>:/home/user/.kube/config

In your config file on the client kit, check that the server_ip is that of your jetson with the server setup.
